We can easily pass data between actvities using Intent(putExtra method)
E.g.
Intent i = new Intent(this,MainActivity2.class);
i.putExtra("Variable Name","Value");
startActivity(i);

Yes, it is not necessary that an Activity should always have a UI.
Foe e.g To Display a Toast from an Activity without layout you would define the activity in your manifest like so:
public class MainActivity extends Activity {
    @Override
    protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
        Toast.makeText(this, "I'm alive", Toast.LENGTH_LONG).show();
        finish();
    }
}

Also the Programmer can omit the UI and do some background functionalities within an activity.
But generally using Servies for that purpose is the prefered option.
